About this item

  • SMARTPHONE MEMORIES MADE REAL: Using the Polaroid ZIP is fast and easy! Just connect a smart phone or tablet via Wi-Fi and watch your portraits, selfies, and social media photos transform from digital images to physical pictures in an instant.
  • STUNNINGLY VIBRANT PRINTS: ZINK ZERO INK printing technology eliminates the need for film, ink, toners, cartridges, and ribbons. The premium 2x3ʺ sticky peel-back paper prints are not only colourful, bold, and lifelike, but are also water-resistant, tear-resistant, smudge-proof, and dry to the touch.
  • FREE POLAROID MOBILE APP: Take your photography to the next level by downloading the FREE Polaroid app, compatible with iOS and Android. No computer connections needed– download the app and unlock all the customizable and adjustable editing features Polaroid has to offer. From stickers to filters to borders, photo editing is easy, fun, and as endless as your creativity.
  • TRAVEL-READY DESIGN: The mini and pocket sized design is compact, super portable and perfect for anyone who loves to travel, blog, do DIY projects, or go on adventures. The small size makes it easy to carry, so you can share your favorite pictures whether you’re indoors, outdoors, at a party, on vacation, or at any other event.

From the manufacturer

Polaroid Zip App

Previous page

  1. Expert Editing

    The Polaroid Zip app provides more than the standard crop and rotate options. Get the picture-perfect print by adjusting brightness, color temperatures, blur settings, and more.

  2. Creative Collages

    Print up to four images on a single photo with the app’s collage mode. Momentous photo montages are just a moment away.

  3. Fantastic Filters + Frames

    Set the mood with the app’s wide array of unique filters. Then add a fun frame to finish off your photo.

  4. So Many Stickers

    Add some goofy fun to your Polaroid prints by adding themed stickers directly from the Polaroid Zip app.

  5. Dazzling Doodles

    Use your phone’s touchscreen to draw directly on your photos. From pictures to messages to smiley faces, the possibilities are only limited by your own creativity.

Next page

Instant Printing Perfection

Previous page

  1. On-the-Go Printing

    Pack the Polaroid Zip in your pocket and you’re ready to print anytime, anywhere.

  2. Print from your Phone

    The Polaroid Zip connects wirelessly with Bluetooth, so there’s no computers needed.

  3. Print and Post

    Polaroid Zip photos are sticky-backed, so you can post them on notebooks, laptops, and more.

  4. Plenty of Prints

    The powerful built-in battery supports up to 25 prints on a single charge.

ZINK Zero Ink Technology

Previous page

  1. Green-Friendly Photos

    No cumbersome cartridges required. By removing the need for ink and toner, ZINK paper cuts down on the waste that goes into landfills, resulting in a happier, healthier planet.

  2. Lifeproof Prints

    Every shot from your Polaroid Zip printer is made to last a lifetime. Each 2x3ʺ sheet is treated with a protective layer that shields it from tears, water damage, and smudges.

  3. Made in the USA

    The ZINK development and manufacturing facility is located in Whitsett, North Carolina. That’s where each sheet of ZINK paper is carefully created by American hands.

  4. Inkless Printing

    No need for ink, toner, or cartridges: ZINK paper is all you need. That’s because each sheet is embedded with color crystals that automatically activate every time you take a picture.

  5. Highly Detailed Prints

    Enjoy vibrant full-color instant photos with a level of detail only possible through ZINK ZERO INK Technology.

Next page

Simple Setup For Fast Photos

Previous page

  1. Step One

    Open paper tray. Insert Polaroid ZINK Paper. Ensure blue calibration sheet is at the bottom.

  2. Step Two

    Press and hold power button. The light will turn on, indicating the device is on.

  3. Download App

    Download Polaroid Zip App from Google Play Store or Apple App Store.

  4. Step Four

    Use the app to personalize photos. Then tap the print button to watch your photos come to life!

Next page
1 Load Paper 2 Power On 3 Download App 4 Edit + Print

What makes the Polaroid Zip unique?

The Polaroid Zip makes it possible to print any picture on your phone or social media account. Add a mountain of editing features, and this portable printer becomes a handheld print studio.

Does the Polaroid Zip come with ZINK paper?

The Polaroid Zip comes with a starter pack of ZINK paper, so you can start printing pictures right away.

Is the Polaroid Zip App required in order to use this printer?

Yes. The Polaroid Zip app must be installed on an Apple or Android device in order to edit and print photos.

Can I print photos that are on my social media page?

Yes. The Polaroid Zip app allows you to access photos from social media, so you can then edit, save, and print them.

Do I need to replace the batteries?

This printer comes equipped with a rechargeable battery, so there’s no need to replace it. The Polaroid Zip can print up 25 photos before it needs to be recharged with the included charging cable.

    4 Stars
    Polaroid Zip Instant Printer
    Firstly, this review is of my opinion. I am a fashion and advertising photographer so I therefore look for clarity and good colour reproductions in images.Overview:For what this little printer is, it isn't too bad! For my intended use, it may perhaps suffice but it could certainly be better.Positives:- Small physical size (very)- Great Portability- Rechargable unremovable battery (unlike closest competitor). Could also be a negative for some- Small images (wallet size - can be seen as good and bad)- Quick to print (despite other reviews the speed isn't bad)- Good accompanying app (could be improved - see negatives)Negatives:- The image size would be nicer if it was a bit bigger (for me personally).- The clarity/sharpness of the prints isn't great, though for what the Polaroid Zip is, perhaps I'm asking too much of it (it's more of a fun, consumer product than a pro printer after-all).- The colour reproduction is off, producing a magenta tinge to images (even black and whites come out with a red/magenta tinge, and even also a little blue).- The App: When resizing images in the 'edit image' portion, unfortunately there is no way of centering the image (either on the horizontal or vertical axis (a method similar to that of Microsoft words image positioning would be ideal)- The battery isn't removable, so if you're in the wild with no mains you cannot remove it and put in another precharged battery like you can with the Zips closest competitor. What you can however do is print and charge at the same time, so try a battery pack for charging phones/laptops etc (i.e search Anker on Amazon).The Polaroid Zip instant printer isn't a bad product. The ease of use and portability makes it a superb product, it is however let down by its image quality (though only slightly). My review is therefore a 4* and not 5*.

    Laz Man
    5.0 out of 5 stars Brilliant. Compact. Easy to set up and no faffing with ink. A brilliant little solution.
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 29 December 2015
    Colour Name: RedStyle Name: 2 x 3 PrinterVerified Purchase
    Bought as a present for my wife. Since our baby was born her phone has become filled with photos and I didn't want them to remain stuck there forever. This is a brilliant little solution. The printer itself is a bit bigger than a boxed deck of cards. Slightly shorter but wider than an iPhone and about twice as thick. It's charged via a usb and you fill it with packs of paper, 10 sheets at a time. These are not mega cheap but the best I found was 7 packs of 10 for £9.
    When charged you just turn the printer on (there is only 1 button on the printer) and use the Polaroid ZIP app to make and send your photo. The app allows you to select single pics or make a collage style photo. The app also allows for some editing like crop, rotate, brightness and contrast, colour balance as well as Instagram-style filters (retro, black and white, cool, sepia, etc).
    The pics take about 20 seconds to print and work via some special chemicals and heat to define the colours rather than ink or toner.
    We've been able to pair 2 iPhones to it via bluetooth and I've just had to select it again from my devices as it was showing but not connected.
    All in all this will be perfect for adding small pics to thank you cards, sticking into her baby book (they are self adhesive peel and stick) and just having as printed photos. The photos are pretty small 2x3 inches (5x7.7cm) but do the job for what we want. Think there's a larger 3x5 version on the way but that's only from looking at the paper stock. There's also a ZINK printer that uses a roll of this type of paper but that's around £200.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Please be wary. See end of review
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 8 January 2016
    Colour Name: BlueStyle Name: 2 x 3 PrinterVerified Purchase
    Beautiful photo printer!
    So cute, and although dimensions were expected, I still wasn't prepared for just how compact it is!
    Actual blue isn't quite as vibrant as shown; it's a bit dull and not quite glossy.
    My daughter had the black coloured version and that one is glossy and as seen in other pictures.

    Very easy to use, though having more than one device connected at once can cause a few problems - this is easily overcome by taking to the other people who are connected and taking turns to send and print! (We got this at Christmas and we were all trying to send images at the same time!).
    Highly recommended.
    Oh, be sure to keep the blue card that comes with the photo paper as you will then be able to use the cheaper Pogo paper from Polaroid earlier edition printers!

    This is updated after receiving this item.
    I now have used 3 of these printers, and it seems the print quality is not consistent.
    One I've sent back because the prints are a few shades darker than expected and shown on phone.
    If I only had encountered one printer, I would not have known this, although i was not happy with the print from the defective one anyway as it was too dark.

    I'd recommend asking for a replacement if you feel the print is not as good as it should be.
    I am very happy with the prints from other machines as they are crisp and bright as expected.
    This printer can deliver, so if it doesn't for you, the device could be faulty.

    Overview:

    - Rechargable unremovable battery (unlike closest competitor). Could also be a negative for some
    - Small images (wallet size - can be seen as good and bad)
    - Quick to print (despite other reviews the speed isn't bad)
    - Good accompanying app (could be improved - see negatives)

    Negatives:
    - The image size would be nicer if it was a bit bigger (for me personally).
    - The clarity/sharpness of the prints isn't great, though for what the Polaroid Zip is, perhaps I'm asking too much of it (it's more of a fun, consumer product than a pro printer after-all).
    - The colour reproduction is off, producing a magenta tinge to images (even black and whites come out with a red/magenta tinge, and even also a little blue).
    - The App: When resizing images in the 'edit image' portion, unfortunately there is no way of centering the image (either on the horizontal or vertical axis (a method similar to that of Microsoft words image positioning would be ideal)
    - The battery isn't removable, so if you're in the wild with no mains you cannot remove it and put in another precharged battery like you can with the Zips closest competitor. What you can however do is print and charge at the same time, so try a battery pack for charging phones/laptops etc (i.e search Anker on Amazon).

    The Polaroid Zip instant printer isn't a bad product. The ease of use and portability makes it a superb product, it is however let down by its image quality (though only slightly). My review is therefore a 4* and not 5*.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty good device but skip the app
    Reviewed in the United States on 28 August 2020
    Colour Name: WhiteStyle Name: 2 x 3 PrinterVerified Purchase
    This is perfect for printing wallet sized photos. The app it suggests you use, don't even bother. It's not user friendly, needs to update before EVERY use (even tho I've already spent 15 min installing the update), and it just doesn't work. The DEVICE however works fairly well although the pics come out a little dark (think of classic Polaroid pics). I have a Google Pixel 3 so I choose my pic from my camera roll, use a filter that makes the pic brighter (almost washed out but not losing any details), click open the options to send the pic (usually used when I'm attaching the pic to a text message), and click Blutooth. Make sure the device is on, then you can send the pic from your phone via Bluetooth without needing to use their worthless app. PRO TIP: These are wallet size photos so if you have a large detailed photo you're trying to print, keep in mind it's only going to print the center most area of the photo (cutting off edges). You can modify this by screenshotting your pic, editing it to make it zoomed out a bit which creates a thick black border around your original pic, then printing. Since the photo on your phone is more centralized, when it prints, it'll pull more of the image since the black edges will be cut off.
    Hope this helps!!
